---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | GoZeroShot"
  description="Privacy Policy for GoZeroShot engineering services, including what information is collected, how it is used, and how deletion requests are handled."
>
  <main class="main legal-page">
    <section class="legal-shell">
      <a class="back-link" href="/">Back to home</a>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="effective-date">Effective date: March 23, 2026</p>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how GoZeroShot collects, uses, stores, and
        protects information when you use the site or engage GoZeroShot for
        engineering, automation, or integration work.
      </p>

      <h2>Information we collect</h2>
      <p>
        We may collect account information, profile information returned by
        third-party authentication providers such as TikTok, project materials,
        submitted content, and technical data needed to operate the site or
        complete the requested work.
      </p>

      <h2>How we use information</h2>
      <p>
        We use collected information to authenticate users, connect third-party
        accounts, perform requested engineering or publishing workflows, improve
        reliability, and provide support.
      </p>

      <h2>TikTok data</h2>
      <p>
        If you connect your TikTok account, GoZeroShot may access profile details
        and permissions that you explicitly authorize through TikTok's OAuth flow.
        We use that information only to support the workflow you requested, such
        as account connection, profile lookup, or content publishing.
      </p>

      <h2>Sharing of information</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell personal information. We may share information with service
        providers or platform partners only when necessary to complete requested
        work, comply with law, or protect against abuse.
      </p>

      <h2>Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain information only for as long as needed to complete requested
        work, maintain basic records, resolve disputes, or comply with legal
        obligations.
      </p>

      <h2>Your choices</h2>
      <p>
        You may disconnect third-party accounts at any time. You may also request
        deletion of your information by contacting us at the email below.
      </p>

      <h2>Security</h2>
      <p>
        We use reasonable administrative and technical measures to protect data,
        but no system can guarantee absolute security.
      </p>

      <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>
        GoZeroShot is not intended for children under 13, and we do not knowingly
        collect personal information from children.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Continued use of the
        site or related services after an update means the revised policy applies.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Privacy questions or deletion requests can be sent to
        <a href="mailto:alynch@gozeroshot.dev">alynch@gozeroshot.dev</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    display: block;
  }

  .legal-shell {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 18px;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #4a6f98;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  p {
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
  }

  .effective-date {
    color: #6b7280;
  }
</style>
